---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About" description="About this blog and its author.">
  <main class="page-container">
    <article class="prose">
      <h1>About</h1>

      <p>
        This is a personal blog for essays, notes, and technical writing.
        The design prioritises the reading experience above everything else —
        no popups, no tracking, no clutter. Just text.
      </p>

      <h2>Writing here</h2>

      <p>
        Posts cover whatever I find interesting: software, systems, mathematics,
        and occasionally things that resist easy categorisation.
      </p>

      <h2>Colophon</h2>

      <p>
        Built with <a href="https://astro.build">Astro</a>, styled with{' '}
        <a href="https://tailwindcss.com">Tailwind CSS v4</a>, and deployed
        via GitHub Pages. Body text is set in Georgia. Headings use the system
        sans-serif stack. Math is rendered with{' '}
        <a href="https://katex.org">KaTeX</a>. Code is highlighted at build
        time with <a href="https://shiki.style">Shiki</a>. The theme toggle
        ships a small inline script; everything else is CSS-only.
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>
